reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Well, if you're here, you don't have the money for "Noctua" or any of the other over-priced fans that look like they are meant to be in a Gay Parade instead of being functional.Are they the best fans in the world? At $15 for three of them, no, surely you jest.Do They Work? Absolutely. Ive gotten about 9-12 months out of them before the "rattle" syndrome rears its ugly head.To be completely honest, I am a Smoker that cleans my rig (i5 11th Gen, 32Gb, RTX3070) about every 6 months, so.. I keep them clean, and they last about 9-12 months. No complaints for $15 for three at all. Welcome to affording Cheap China. I get it.Im on my 3rd set in about 3-3.5 years or so.. Still, can't complain. $45 for 3+ years compared to the ridiculous prices of some more popular brands... F-it..Do they push a LOT of air? No... but if your rig is set up right, they Don't need to "Push Air" they just need to keep air moving.. and that they do, nicely, and quietly... for about 9-12 months... then its another $15 for 3 of em.. :)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fairly quiet and pushes enough air. White LEDS are also pretty bright and are a nice and true white
reviews.reviewText: The fans are quiet enough and they blow enough air around to keep my PC cool. The white LEDS are nice looking and quite bright. The brightness of the LEDS is controlled by the voltage of course and they are fully bright at around when the fan speed is at 1000rpm but at this rpm the fans aren't that loud so may as well just run them at this rpm all the time so that the PC is always kept cool.Good fans, worth the buy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good fans. However, description did not list type of cable
reviews.reviewText: These fans are great for those on a budget. They are quiet and the LED is bright. However, in the description, the cable type was not mentioned and so it it’s a 3 pin fan cable with a molex connector for the LED lighting, it is also very short so make sure that you have a molex extension in case your molex from the psu isn’t long enough to reach the motherboard. Overall they are good fans and would buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 7, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good value, Works well and really is quiet
reviews.reviewText: replaced a 230mm x 30 700 rpm top case fan. This case is set up for this type of fan or 3 120mm case fans. I only used 2 fans which provided little more air flow and keeps the case cool. I like the 2 plug option so I can choose with what I have available. These have the same 19 dBA rating as my original fan. They are really quiet. I can not hear them over my other existing fans. All the screws were provided, although they are not great, but they did fastened the fans and are holding well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 3, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars plain simple fans that move air and don't rattle
reviews.reviewText: The DIYPC case I purchased has a neat little RGB strip up front and a white reflective mesh to make the whole front end have color. So I figured, it's mesh, it can flow air, why not stick three 120mm fans down the front of it? Enter the upHere 3-pack of 120mm fans. I could've bought Rosewill or Cooler Master or any other number of brands, but they cost more money and don't do anything these can't do.These fans move air into my case, don't make noise, don't rattle, and have all black wiring, screws, and connectors. They look good (because you can't see them, but if you COULD they would look fine). They were no more difficult to install than any other case fan with 4 headless screws. The package included 24 little foam rubber pads to go on the corners. I only needed twelve of these for installation but if I need them for the other side later on down the road, I have extras.I will be purchasing another 3-pack of these soon, because I also put two 120mm fans on the top of my case for exhaust, and they were older Cooler Masters I've had sitting in storage since...uh...2010? So they have ketchup and mustard wiring, silver screws, shiny chrome stickers, and look hideous. I mean they work, and they are on top where I can't see them, but I KNOW they are THERE!Picture shows my computer with no front on it so show the fans spinning silently. If you put your ear to your screen, you can hear how loud they aren't.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Cheap and flimsy, careless QA
reviews.reviewText: No screws were included, despite being listed in the item description.Fans are made of cheap plastic, very flimsy and easy to bend.Installation was made very difficult because of the lack of screws.Best to stick to better-known name brands.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy Plug-N-Play Computer Fix
reviews.reviewText: I noticed that the original cooling fan inside the CPU had stopped working and the computer would overheat and shut down at the most inopportune time. This product, in a three-pak, was less expensive than purchasing a single unit and has the added feature of illumination. Was a simple matter of removing 4 screws and unplugging from the motherboard. Check to see first if your fan is 3- or 4-pin and whether the pins are gapped or equal-distant, then order a replacement that matches what you have. This unit has provisions for both 3- and 4-pin connections.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very quiet. Seems to push enough air to keep everything cool.
reviews.reviewText: I have 3 inlet fans, 2 of them being these. 2 exhaust fans. Positive pressure system and I’m happy with them, Very very quiet. They really don’t push much air so do your own calculations on air flow.
the pins are fairly difficult to mount into the power supply cables, the pins move and shift, be sure they are properly seated. i had to use a screwdriver.
Look good, sound good but one didn't work and they aren't very efficient. My corsair fan would spin faster when connected to a fan controller.
Me gustó el hecho que sean silenciosos, aún llendo al 100%, pero el flujo de aire es poco, sobre todo si la temperatura ambiental es cercana a los 30c
